reviewText: Classic Fred Williamson action from 1973 featuring an eclectic cast - Richard Anderson, Larry D. Mann, Cyril Delevanti, Teresa Graves, Rosemary Forsyth among others plus some good old fashioned fisticuffs. A nice transfer from Warners with solid colors. Enjoy!

Not a bad time filler. No racial stereotypes. A low key Private Eye movie from the 70's good performances, script and overall good production values. I found this movie entertaining and it had fairly good mystery case.
If you liked Robert Mitchum's turn as Phillip Marlow in the 70's then you're bound to like Black Eye.
